			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Indigo is a deep color close to the color wheel blue, based on the ancient dye of the same name. The dye was originally exported to Europe from India. It used to be a natural dye made from Indigofera shrubs. The naturally occurring precursor of indigo is indican, a colourless, water-soluble substance that is easily hydrolyzed to glucose and indoxyl; the latter is converted to indigo by mild oxidation, such as exposure to air.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">靛蓝是一种接近色轮蓝的深色，以古代同名染料为基础。这种染料最初从印度出口到欧洲。它曾经是一种由 Indigofera 灌木制成的天然染料。靛蓝的天然前体是茚满，它是一种无色的水溶性物质，很容易水解为葡萄糖和茚满酮；后者在轻度氧化（如暴露在空气中）后转化为靛蓝。</common:generalComment>
